./proposals/composition_engine.md:225:The Fisher inner product is *just* the choice of `W` inside `WorkingModel::update`. Nothing about REML, IFT, or basis evaluation changes — the standard machinery already differentiates through arbitrary `W` because PIRLS is written for it (`src/solver/pirls.rs:526-529`).
